inn1.comm: back of a length outside off and gets some movement straightaway, zips away from Haddin as he lets it go
short of a length outside off, makes room and chops that towards third man for a single, Australia are away
good carry through to the keeper there, banged in slightly short outside off, left alone
much fuller, bowled on a good length on the off stump, defended wide of midwicket for a single
short of a good length on the off stump, pushes the batsman back who defends it solidly back to the bowler
pushed through a little slower on middle and leg, Haddin walked out of the crease but the bowler chased him, he adjusted well to open the face and guide it to third man
short of a length outside off, moving away a touch, left alone to the keeper
gets forward and turns it wide of midwicket for a quick single
does well, short of a good length on the off stump, dropped between point and cover for a run
bowled from wide of the crease, fullish on the off stump, defended wide of cover
short of a length on middle, gets back and works it away through square leg for a single
fullish on the off stump, driven with a full face towards extra cover who's right at the edge of the circle
bouncer banged in short on middle, Clarke evades it comfortably
short of a length outside off, cutting length that, Clarke restrains himself, lets it go

good length on the off stump from wide of the crease, angling into the batsman, Clarke gets forward to push it into the direction of cover, flips the pads on the way to the keeper, a big appeal but it was neither lbw - would have gone over the stumps -  nor a caught-behind, as there was no inside edge
pushed through fuller on the off stump, reaches forward and bunts it to cover
short on the off, makes room and just chips it over cover for a couple
unlucky, inducing him to drive on the front foot, Clarke obliges but gets an faint inside edge as the ball angles in, it evades the keeper and fine leg to the boundary
back of a length on the off stump and nipping back in in, defended off the back foot
punished, short and wide, makes room and carts it over point and cover for his first boundary
and again, bowled full on middle and off, makes room and slices it over point, he's getting into his groove now
back of a length on middle, defends it watchfully back to the bowler this time
short of a good length on the off stump, defended into the off side
short and wide, gets forward and tries to slash it through the point region, misses and Boucher takes it over his head
fullish on the off stump and moving away, shoulders arms to that one
full outside off stump and zipping in this time, left alone to the keeper
back of a length outside off, gets back and guides it wide of third man
short of a good length outside off, gets forward, waits and crunches it through the covers for a sublime four
tries to do it again but doesn't time it well enough, struck in the direction of mid-off
back of a length on middle, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
full on the off stump, makes way and drags it wide of mid-on , there's a yawning gap between him and midwicket and they get a couple comfortably
fetch that! Just a fraction full on middle, Haddin has made his mind up, makes room and swats it back past the bowler, that was bludgeoned
he's decided to go after Ntini, full again and slogged over midwicket, didn't time it well but the shot was on
held it back this time, on middle, turned it into the leg side for an easy single, sensibly done
full on the off stump, leans into the drive to play it towards a deepish mid-off for a single
angling into middle from wide of the crease, flicked away wide of deep midwicket for three more, nicely timed
short of a length outside off and moves away, left alone to the keeper
squared him up there, banged in short on middle, he tried to defend that inside the line off the back foot but adjusted well in the end as the ball moved away, played it to cover
slower ball bowled on a good length on middle, clipped away nicely off his pads behind square for three more, bowled at 117 kmph
races away, just a fraction short outside off, cracked off the back foot wide of a diving de Villiers at point, he gets his fingers to it but it's struck powerfully, beats him to the ropes
similar delivery but doesn't connect well enough, slashes hard, the ball takes the bottom of the bat and rolls down to third man
fullish on middle, driven wide of mid-on for a single
back of a length on the off stump, run down to third man, brings up the 50 for Australia, breezy start this
short and wide, slashes hard, flies off the outside edge towards third man
Ntini has struggled in this game, short on the off stump, Haddin moves away and slaps it over mid-on for a one bounce four, not a pleasant return for the bowler
fullish on the off stump, cracked to mid-off, good sound of bat hitting ball but the fielder is at the edge of the circle
much straighter on middle this time, makes room and pushes it to extra cover

shot for lbw, gets wide of the crease and bowls it on a good length on middle, nipped back in a touch as it pitched, Clarke got his front foot across and tried to flick that wide of midwicket, missed it and was rapped in front. Steyn goes up immediately, but the umpire says no. Looked pretty adjacent to me
beautifully struck, fullish on middle and leg, takes a couple of steps forward and lofts it over the bowler's head, almost went all the way
bouncer banged in short on middle, more of frustration that, Clarke ducks under it comfortably
short of a length on the off, pushed wide of cover off the back foot for a single
easily done, poor ball really, full on leg stump, Haddin helps it on its way wide of short fine for a boundary
back of a length on the off, chopped down to point
full on middle and leg, looks to slog that over midwicket, mistimes it and rolls along the ground
straight again, gets forward and bunts it to mid-on for a single
full on middle and off, bowled at 141.3 kmph, driven straight to mid-on
back of a length on the off, defended solidly towards cover
good length on the off stump, makes room and strikes it cleanly over mid-off, even Morkel's not being spared
back of a length outside off and moved in, left alone, good comeback
good length outside off, raced off the bat and he just opened the face, third man ran well to his right to cut that off
slower ball bowled short of a length outside off, struck crisply to cover
straying on the pads, worked away uppishly between midwicket and square leg for a single
poor ball, log hop on middle, at a good height to play the pull, Clarke stays in the crease and pulls it away behind square
slower one on middle and leg, pushed through the line to mid-on
slower one again, bowled at 99.4 kmph, driven wide of Kallis for a single to long-on
short of a length outside, backed away to go for a powerful cut, missed it
short again, pushed wide of cover off the back foot
short of a length on middle, gets back and pushes it in the direction of mid-on for a single
good length on the off stump, closes the face to work it away to square leg
classy, full and wide but Clarke has Morkel flummoxed as he shuffles outside off and clips it away wide of short fine for a boundary
slightly short on the off, tries to punch it through cover, gets a thick inside edge in the direction of mid-on
it's raining fours here, short of a length outside off, Haddin makes room to cut that past point, gets a thick edge wide of a diving Boucher to beat third man
slower one bowled full on the off, picked it up early, spotted it well and just lofted it with ease over mid-on to bring up his half-century in style, excellent stuff
back of a length on the off, turned away to square leg
slightly short on middle, pushed off the back foot wide of the bowler for a single to long-on
slower one bowled short on leg stump, worked away behind square
shortish on middle, punched off the back foot in the direction of extra cover
landed on a good length outside off, gets way outside the line to turn it wide of mid-on, is struck on the pads, gets a couple of leg byes
short and wide, that should have disappeared and Clarke is rightly upset for having missed out, makes room to cut and misses, probably bounced more than he had expected
good length on the off, dropped short of cover for a quick single
missed out again, juicy outside leg stump, most batsmen would have clipped it fine but Haddin misses
fullish on the off stump, presents the full face to drive it into the infield on the off side
short of a length on the off stump, walks across and tries to paddle it over short fine, fails to connect well, salvages a run
starts with a rank log hop on middle, Boucher is standing up, pulled away wide of deep square leg for a single
atrocious fielding by his brother, turned away towards him at short fine, he bends low to field and lets it slip through his fingers to the fine-leg boundary, fifty up for Clarke
pushed off the back foot into the off side for a single
short outside off, looks to heave it over midwicket, is into the shot a little too early
good length on middle, pushed back past the bowler for a single to long-on
the punishment continues, just a fraction short, but a little too wide, Clarke reaches for it and square-drives it to bisect the gap between cover and point
short of a length outside off, guided down to third man for a single
short of a length outside off, makes room and cuts it hard towards Gibbs at short cover who does a superb job getting his body behind it to save a four
short on middle and leg, paddled down behind square for a single
full on middle and leg, almost yorker length, dug out wide of square leg
on middle and off, tries to drive it in the cover region, gets a thick inside edge behind square for a single
short of a length, much closer to the off stump, chopped down to third man
shot of the day, tossed up on the off stump, gives himself some space and creams it through the gap between cover and mid-off, the crowd is mum
tossed up on middle, pushed back to the bowler
dipping into the right hander, driven hard but straight towards extra cover
short on middle and leg, punched down the ground to long-on
quicker one bowled full on the off stump, pushed towards extra cover, good comeback after being hit for four off the first ball
short of a length outside off, chopped down towards point
short again but on the stumps, defended watchfully
better, bowled at 137.8 kmph, cramping Haddin for room here, on middle and leg, turned to midwicket, three dot balls
and one more, much fuller, driven back to the bowler who fields well on the follow through
straying on the pads and Haddin misses out, tries to glance it fine, misses and is hit on the legs
Well done, Morne! Full on the off stump, driven straight to Gibbs at short cover, the first maiden of the day and the crowd cheer as though he has just taken a wicket
flighted on the off stump, is down the track and drives it through the line to long-off
quicker one bowled on middle and leg, defended with a big stride forward
flat and quick outside off, pushed into the off side wide of cover
flighted on middle and leg and angling down, tries to drive it past midwicket, is hit on the pads
flighted on middle, comes down the track and drives it to cover
spoils a good over, short on middle and spins away, makes room and cuts it away well wide of point

he's got him! SA following up well on that maiden,  full on the off stump, Haddin makes room to cart that over the infield on the off side, ends up slicing it really high and Duminy at deep cover, positioned perfectly, just had to take few steps to his right to complete an easy catch
yorker on middle, dug out well into the off side and he jams his bat into the pitch soon after playing the shot, the bat splits and he's called for a change
full on middle and leg, driven through the line to long-on
fullish on the off stump, pushed through into the off side
yorker length on middle, dug out towards mid-on, good stuff from Albie
beaten! Held it back just a touch and got it to move away from Ponting who was sucked into the drive, hung his bat out and missed
quicker one bowled full on middle, comes down the track and pushes it to midwicket
short and wide, makes room for a cut, spins away and keeps a touch low to beat the outside edge
flat on the off stump, is down the track and bunts it to long-off
tossed up, lands on a teasing length outside off and spins away sharply to beat Ponting as gets forward to defend
quicker one bowled full on the off, pushed to cover
finds the gap this time, crunches it through the infield towards deep cover to get off the mark
full on the off stump, driven back to the bowler
good length on the off, pushed off the front foot to mid-off again, South Africa have pulled things back somewhat after drinks
full and wide, gets forward to tries to drive it through the covers, goes at it hard but the away movement beats him
on middle and off, pushed wide of the bowler towards long-on
full on middle and leg, driven through the line to long-on
will he regret doing that now? Full on the off stump, Ponting drives at it hard, the ball kisses the outside edge and rolls down the third-man boundary
tossed up on middle and leg, comes down the track and drives it to deep midwicket
short of a length outside off, kept a little low as Ponting made room for a cut, just missed the off stump
flighted on the off, driven through the line to long-off
short of a length on the middle stump, defended off the back foot towards cover

Clarke goes! Pushed in short on middle, Clarke got on the front foot and pulled it straight o Duminy, running to his right from deep square leg, not a fully committed pull that, more a short-arm one and though he timed it well, he couldn't get the distance
tossed up outside leg, swept straight to short fine
bowled on a good length on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, gets back, and opens the face to guide it perfectly in the gap between third man and deep point, the quick outfield did the rest
punched into the off side on the back foot, slightly short again
fuller on the off stump, pushed in the direction of point off the front foot
slightly overpitched on middle, turned away wide of midwicket in front of mid-on for a single
full on the off stump, Ponting gets to the pitch and punches it to deep cover
short outside leg stump, tries to paddle it down fine, plays it onto his pads but gets a single
quicker one bowled full on the off stump, tries to drive it with a full face, gets an inside edge onto his pads
worked away behind square for a single
quicker one on middle and leg, dabbed at it hard, lobbed up well in front of midwicket
fullish on leg stump, tickled wide of square leg
quicker one, full on the off, chipped wide of Ntini at long-off, he's a little late onto it and they get an easy couple
full on the off stump, closes the face to play it wide of midwicket for a single
well bowled, short on the off and came back in, the movement caught Ponting by surprise, played it well in the end, dropping it down with soft hands behind point
short on the off stump, played it deliberately, waited for it come to him and opened the face at the last moment to beat the keeper, and third man, to the boundary
banged in short on the off stump, Ferguson leapt to drop it down the on the off side, it caught the high-end of the bat to fall just short of point

unlucky! Ferguson had already made room and Ntini tried to follow him, pitched in short on middle and leg, the batsman tried to dab it into the off side, got the inside edge to just evade the leg stump and beat the fine-leg fielder
pushed off the front foot wide of short midwicket for a single
on middle and leg, worked away towards short fine
tossed up on middle, driven hard but straight to short midwicket
pushed into the off side towards point
comes down the track and drives it down the ground to long-on
short on leg stump, whipped away to deep square leg
full outside leg stump, tickled to short fine, no run though, good over from the part-timer
full outside off, driven off the front foot wide deep cover but the fielder does well to rocket a good throw back in to keep them down to just a run
overpitched again, square-driven straight to de Villiers at point who dives well to his right to prevent a couple of runs
much straighter on middle this time, struck hard towards midwicket, a fumble following a valiant dive allows them a single
a touch too wide this time , sliced into the gap between third man and deep point for a couple
back of a length on the off and darting back in, dropped into the leg side
superb shot, was aiming for the yorker then, fired it full on middle, Ferguson made room and drilled it wide of cover, timing it beautifully to beat both deep cover and long-off
short on middle and leg, turned away wide of short fine
pitched in short outside off, waited for it to spin into him and chopped it behind point for a couple
cramped him for space this time, fired in on middle and leg, dropped onto the pitch
worked away off the back foot into the leg side for a single
punched to long-on for a single
and again, flighted and full on the off, gets forward and pushes through the line to long-on
short and quick outside off, cut away in front of cover for a couple
too wide, short and wide, cut away hard behind point, these two have helped their team recover well after that post-drinks wobble
tossed up on middle, struck cleanly to long-off
short on middle and off, pushed wide of cover for a single
cut away again but not as well, gets a single wide of point
flighted on middle, driven down the ground to long-on
tossed up on middle, chips it over the infield but falls just short of deep midwicket
pushed back off the front foot to the bowler
on middle and leg, bunts it down to long-on
sliding on the pads, turned away to deep square leg
the same fielder back in action, short on leg stump, slaps it into the deep
Fergie goes! An abrupt end to a good stand, quicker one the off stump, lands full, he drives through the line but ends up chipping it straight to de Villiers at short cover who takes a sharp chance
over the wicket to the left hander, landed on a good length outside off and spun in, defended back to the bowler
slightly short on middle and off, dabbed back to the bowler
fuller on the off, gets forward and pushes it wide of cover to get off the mark
on the stumps, pitched on a good length, Ponting defends with a lunge
tossed up on middle, a low full toss, pushed back to van der Merwe, an excellent over that
flighted on middle, dipping into the left hander, defended towards cover
thrown up on the leg stump this time, pushed to midwicket
flighted on the off stump, bunts it down the ground to long-off
short of a length outside off, gets back and punches it to deep cover
tossed up on the off stump, gets forward and presents the full face but fails to beat the bowler
short on leg stump, gets on the back foot and tickles it behind square
short of a length on the off and spinning in, pushed back to Hussey
short on middle, punched off the back foot to midwicket
pushed through the line to long-off
slightly short on the off stump, moves back and chops it wide of deep point for a couple
tossed up on middle, comes forward and chips it uppishly, just wide of AB at short cover for a single wide of long-off
on middle and off, defended off the front foot to short cover
flighted on middle, driven down the ground to long-on
tossed up on the off, comes down the track and pushes it wide of Duminy for a single
flighted on middle, gets across the line and dabs it behind square
quicker through the air, and bowled flatter on the off stump, tries to chop it down wide of point, gets an inside edge onto his pads
flighted outside off, goes at it hard, more out desperation, ends up slicing it high but falls safely short of deep cover
pushed through to long-on off the front foot
short of a length on the off, dropped short of cover for a quick single
short of a length outside off, guided past slip towards third man
short and wide, cut away to point, struck down hard but straight to the fielder
Ponting's lucky, it's full and wide and he is tempted into the drive, the ball holds its line and he gets an inside edge wide of a diving keeper to the fine-leg boundary
banged in short on middle this time, gets back and pulls it away to deep square leg
bouncer, misdirected, down the leg side and it's given a wide, the first of the innings
fired in on leg stump, tucked away in the vacant gap between fine leg and square leg, the fielder from the deep takes a while running in and they grab a couple
short of a length on middle, gets forward to turn it fine, gets a top edge but wide of short fine for a single
short of a length outside off, cut away towards point where a slightly fumble by Smith allows them to sneak a single
Big one! Flighted outside off, charges down the track and smashes it into the stands over the bowler's head, finally!

tossed up on the stumps this time and is tempted to go at it again, strikes it clean and high but not well enough as he fails to beat van der Merwe at long-on who takes a well-judged catch. Duminy does the trick.
dropped, quicker one bowled full outside off, driven uppishly wide of de Villiers who flings himself to his left at short cover but fails to latch on to a sharp one
driven down the ground towards long-off for a single
on the stumps, tucked away towards fine leg for a single
back of a length outside off, David Hussey lets it go
short on middle, worked away towards deep square leg to get off the mark
shortish on the off stump, chopped down to third man
a touch fuller and much straighter, on middle and off, defended in the direction of cover
short on middle, pulled away wide of deep midwicket for a couple
quicker one bowled on the off, pushed to cover
flighted on middle, looks to paddle it fine, gets the top edge onto his body and the ball lobs up in front of short fine

a leg-side stumping, tossed up on middle and leg, drawing David Hussey out of the crease as he tries to work that away behind square, the ball spins down, the batsman misses and Boucher clips the bails to find him well short
tossed up on middle, pushed through to midwicket
wide down the leg side again, spinning sharply to beat Boucher and they get three more
short of a length outside off, cut away off the back foot wide of point
another one, it's brought them a wicket but he's doing it too often

AB you beauty! Pushed wide of him at short cover but Hopes is not quick enough to respond, AB picks it up cleanly and throws down the stumps and the striker's end, while still diving forward, to find Hopes short of his ground
pushed into the off side for a single wide of cover
tucked away behind square to get off the mark
short on middle and Hussey cashes in, picks the length early to rock back and bisect the gap between long-on and deep midwicket
short of a length outside off, dabbed towards short third
quicker one pushed through full outside off, spins away and Johnson lets it go
drive through the line towards long-off for a single to give Hussey the strike
short of a length, chopped down to deep cover
tossed up on middle, pushed back firmly but straight to the bowler

short on middle, pushes it back uppishly towards Duminy who dives forward and to his left to pluck it inches off the ground, or so it seemed. Duminy wasn't sure himself and asked the umpire to call for a replay, which then confirmed he had just about managed to get his hands around it.
tossed up on middle and leg, tickled to short fine
tossed up on middle and leg, lipped off his pads to deep midwicket
short on the off stump, punched off the back foot to short cover
short on the off, guided wide of point for a single
quicker one bowled on a good length on the off, driven down the ground to long-on
angling into the batsman from round the wicket, flighted on middle, defended to cover
flighted outside off, drawing him into the drive, the ball spins away to beat the outside edge and Boucher takes off the bails, but Hauritz has dragged his foot back in time
on middle and leg, played away straight to midwicket
driven off the front foot to long-on for a single
flighted on middle and off, tries to swat it wide of cover, gets a thick inside edge behind square for a single
back of a length on the off, guided off the back foot to third man
short of a good length on middle and off, defended in the direction of cover
slower ball bowled on a good length on the off, cuts away as Hussey hangs his bat out to defend
zipped back in from outside off to clip Hussey's bat on the way to the keeper, he was surprised by the movement and failed to get his bat behind in time
short of a good length on middle and off, defended in the direction of cover
flighted on the off stump, driven to long-off
on the off again, reaches forward to defend
short of a length outside off, tries to guide it behind point, misses
low full toss on the off stump, driven down to long-on
short on the off stump, pulled away to deep midwicket
quicker one bowled full on leg stump, played back to Duminy
slower ball bowled short outside leg stump, Hussey tries to pull it fine, gloves it into the ground towards a diving Boucher
short on middle, pulled away to deep midwicket
short of a length outside off, but a little too wide, chases it but fails to connect
bouncer banged in short on middle, ducks under it comfortably
short on the off stump, dabs it off the back foot to point to give Hussey the strike
another wide, down the leg side this time, Hussey tries to get his bat to it but doesn't connect
and again, poor bowling this, attempted the slower one this time but got his direction totally wrong
full on the off stump, plays a well-timed drive down the ground to long-off
beaten! Short of a good length outside off and moves away just a touch to beat the outside edge as he gets back to defend
poor ball first up, short outside leg stump and Hussey gets back and across to help it on its way over short fine for a much-needed four
struck away into the deep towards the cover for a single
slower one on
good length on the off, gets forward to drive to down to mid-off
short on the off stump and Ntini makes a mess at mid-on, it's swatted straight towards him but he lets it go through diving to his right, he's had a bad game
full on the off, creamed through to deep cover off the front foot
good length outside off, it's a little wide, Hussey reaches for it to play it wide of cover for a quick single
on middle and leg, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
slower ball bowled full outside off, an offcutter that leaves Hussey as he tries to waft that over midwicket, handy delivery that
lovely stuff, totally deceived Hussey with the slower one this time, banged in short on the off stump and cut away as he tried to slap that over the infield on the leg side
finds the gap this time, dropped his pace once again but Hussey expected that, waited for it and cut it away off the back foot into the vacant cover region on the off side
full on middle and leg, was in the slot, a length ball that, tried to smash it over midwicket, ended up getting an inside edge just wide of leg stump
dropped by Steyn at fine leg, short on middle, tried to pull it over square leg got the top edge but Steyn at fine leg spilled a relatively easy chance running to his right
short outside off, goes for the pull again but fails to connect
pushed off the front foot wide of long-off for a couple
full on middle and leg, length ball, and gets the treatment, Hussy plants his front foot forward and strikes it in the gap between long-on and deep midwicket for a one bounce four
full and wide, makes room, chases it, but fails to reach
straying on the pads and Hauritz gets into the act, finally, full on the leg stump, clipped wide of short fine to the fine-leg boundary
has a blind waft to a good length ball outside off, misses it completely
slower ball on middle that he picked pretty early, made room and struck it cleanly over long-on into the stands, he's made up somewhat after struggling for most of this innings, 300 up
full on the off stump, makes room and steers it wide of point for a single
full outside off, slashed towards point where Gibbs keeps them down to a single
full and wide, swings hard but makes no contact, they run through for a bye

inn2.comm: Johnson starts off with a back of the length ball that thuds into Gibbs' pads and rolls away to square leg
much fuller and just outside off, Gibbs reaches out and jabs that towards cover
wider outside off, Gibbs isn't interested in playing that one, lets it through to the keeper
Gibbs get going with a glorious drive through the covers which has the crowd roaring, it was overpitched and there was some width, Gibbs  eased that through the off side
on the pads this time, Gibbs turns it away to fine leg to get himself an easy single
short of a good length outside off, coming in a touch, Gibbs shoulders arms
good length on middle and leg, turned away wide of square leg for a single
good length on the off and moving away a touch, defended to cover off the back foot
shaping away from the right hander, fullish outside off, Smith is not sucked into the drive through, he chooses to let it go
slightly sort outside off, dabbed down to third man, just wide of second slip, deliberately done
swinging in, landing on middle and leg but was going down as Gibbs missed an attempted flick to be struck on the pads
full on the off stump, opens the face at the last moment to play it down to third man
goes for a mighty heave over midwicket, though he was nowhere near it, slightly short outside off, much slower through the air and missed it completely
good length on the off stump, moving a touch into the right hander, pushed straight to mid-off
full on the off stump, pushed past the bowler wide of a diving mid-off, who's not standing as deep as he usually does, for three runs
straying on the pads, tickled behind square wide of fine leg for a couple more
full and straight on middle, defended off the front foot, presents the full face as he plays it back to the bowler
good length on middle and leg, swinging down, turned to square leg
short of a good length on the off stump, dabbed into the off side towards cover
pitched outside leg and moved into Gibbs who tried to clip it fine, but was hit on the pads
mid-on's right at the edge of the circle and is in perfect position to stop a flowing drive from Gibbs on the up
good length outside off, held its line and Gibbs opted not to play
good length on middle and moving into Gibbs, dropped dead on the pitch, maiden by Bracken, good stuff
short outside off, goes for the cut but fails to reach, it's too wide anyway
angling into the right hander, a touch too straight there, in Smith's zone and he works it away behind square for a couple
short on middle, Smith got back to play of his trademark whips off the pads, got an inside edge onto his thighs
touch fuller on the off, the bat turns in his hands as he tries to push it through the off side, gets a single wide of mid-on
short on the off, charges down the track and slaps it straight to mid-on, a hint of desperation there
shot, good length outside off, eases through the drive to place it perfectly between short cover and cover point, that was all timing, just a firm push
that's disappeared! Short on middle, Gibbs rocks back and pulls it away with disdain into the stands over square leg for a flat six. He's on track now
Smith follows that dismissive six with a textbook drive wide of mid-on, pitched up outside off, leans forward and caresses that to the boundary
short and wide, makes room and cuts it away powerfully over point, leapt as he got cart that over the infield
gets it much straight on middle, turned away wide of square leg for a single
full toss on leg stump, Gibbs just flicks it straight to square leg where a misfield allows him to steal two, but it was a poor ball though, he'll feel he missed out

edged and four, full outside off, inviting him to drive, he tries to play that though the covers but a hint of away movement leads him to edge that just wide of a diving Haddin to the third-man boundary
false start, full and wide and swinging away further, deservedly called a wide
much better, slightly short of a good length on the off and moved away sharply to beat the outside edge as Gibbs got back to defend
the Wanderers roars as Gibbs charges down the track and an overpitched ball and smashes it over mid-off for his third four
a probing line outside off this time, is tempted to push at it but the movement almost does him in
short of a length on the off, defended to cover
full and wide, tries to bludgeon it over mid-off again, misses
good length on middle, gets forward and defends it to midwicket

edged and gone! Bowled on a good length outside off, Smith took a couple of steps forward and simultaneously made room to slice that over the infield on the off side, got a thick edge and Haddin did the rest
shaky start, gets an inside edge to fine leg as he tries to play forward
short of a length outside off, held its line, left alone
short on middle, gets back and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
bowled at 132.6 kmph, lands short of a good length outside off, left alone
back of a length again, punched towards cover off the back foot
good length on the off stump, defended watchfully back to Laughlin
bowled on a length again, but much straighter, on middle and leg, presents the full face to play it past the bowler for a single
short of a length outside off and nipping back in, Kallis shoulders arms
tries to drive it on the up, gets an inside edge onto the pads and rushes for a single as it drops short of Ponting at cover
defended off the back foot in the direction of point, held it back a touch this time
short and wide, looks to cut that fiercely through point but it's a little out of his reach as a result of the away movement
banged in short, rolled his wrists over it to chop it behind point for a couple wide of third man
imperious, just a fraction overpitched outside off, held its line and Kallis, half-forward, drove it firmly through the line between extra cover and mid-off
back of a length, chops it down towards deep point for a single
straying on the pads, tickled to short fine, failed to beat the gap
teasing line outside off, leaving the right hander but Gibbs restrains himself, letting it go
bowled on a good length on the off, gets front and across and pushes it back to the bowler
banged in short and Kallis is onto it quickly, spots the length early, gets back and pulls it away well wide of deep square leg for a six
good length outside off and angling away, left alone to the keeper
length ball on the off stump, mistimes a drive back to the bowler who palms it to mid-off
on the off stump, bowled from a touch wide of the crease, driven firmly but straight to Ponting at short cover
full on the off stump, dropped between point and cover for a quick single to keep the strike
bangs it in slightly short on middle, Kallis moves across and whips it off his hips wide of a diving fine leg, who puts in a good effort diving to his right but ends up palming it to the boundary
came back in this time, short of a length on the off and struck Kallis on the ribs as he tried to work that away
short of a length on leg stump, turned wide of square leg for a single

almost had him there, good length outside off, Gibbs came down the track and tried to clear mid-off while reaching for it after he had made room, hit the bottom-end of the bat and landed just short of Ferguson at mid-off who dived forward but failed to get to it
slightly short on leg stump, tries to turn it behind square, ends up dropping it on the pitch, calls for a run but is sent back
trying to draw him forward, bowling it on a good length outside off, Gibbs opts to let it go
pitched up on the off stump, gets forward and drives it to deep cover for a single
full on middle and leg, turned away wide of deep square leg
short of a length outside off, chopped down to point where Clarke fields and shies at the stumps at the non-striker's end
back of a length again, pushed through to cover
much straighter, bowled on middle, driven straight to midwicket
yorker on middle, dug out back to the bowler, was right in the blockhole but Kallis did well to bring his bat down in time
dragged it a little short, made room to cut it to point
good length on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
down the leg side, tries to help it on its way to fine leg, clips the thighs on the way to the keeper
short of a good length on the off, dabbed down to third man for a single
a touch lucky, banged in short on middle, Kallis attempts to pull it behind square, the ball probably got onto him a little too quickly, got the top edge over the keeper's head for a boundary
short of a length on the off, punched to cover
pushed through quick but Gibbs ends up converting it into an overpitched delivery, taking a couple of steps forward to get under it and drive it uppishly past mid-on
full on the off stump, reaches forward and pushes it to cover
bowled on a length again, square-drives it wide of cover but fails to beat the gap
slightly short outside off, a slower ball that, hangs his bat out to drop it behind point for a single, rolled his wrists over it to keep it down
pays the price for feeding him with a length ball on his pads, Kallis has no trouble to clip it wide of short fine
long hop on the off stump, pulled away wide of deep square leg who attempts to stop it lethargically reaching for it to his right, but fails to get to it
pushed in quicker on the off stump, played to midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
tossed up outside off, eased through the infield on the off side to deep cover
flatter on the off stump, dropped wide of cover for a single to keep the strike
overpitched outside of, driven along the ground wide of deep cover
angling into Kallis who closes the face to nudge that behind square for a single
beaten as he tries to dab that to third man, short of a good length and he chases it, only to be beaten by the hint of away movement
moving back in this time, turns it to midwicket off the back foot
swipes it away for a boundary wide of short fine to bring up 8000 ODI runs, just a fraction overpitched and he does it easily moving front and across
short of a length outside off, tries to heave it into the leg side, misses
pushed off the front foot towards long-on
straying on the pads, paddles it really fine, well wide of fine leg for two more
flat and full on middle, turned to midwicket
flighted on middle, comes down the track and drives it down to long-on
tossed up outside off, driven through the line to cover
back of a length on the off, gets forward and punches it to mid-off
short of a length on the off stump, slower one that, bowled at 113.5 kmph, punched to deep cover
in the channel outside off, Kallis blocks it in front of cover
fullish on the pads, clipped away to deep square leg
third man into the action now, just a fraction short outside off, guided to him off the back foot
on middle and off, pushed through off the front foot to cover
gets forward and turns it down to square leg

missed stumping, landed on a good length outside off, drew Gibbs out of his crease as he tries to play it into the off side, misses as the ball doesn't turn, Haddin fails to collect it cleanly as it bounces off his gloves back onto the pitch
short on middle and leg, hit on the thighs as he tries to play that off the back foot
pushed off the front foot in the direction of deep cpver
driven through the off side towards long-off
straying on the pads, paddles it fine to move to 49
flighted on the off stump, eased wide of cover to reach his fifty, a touch fortunate after that missed stumping, how costly will it prove?
driven off the front foot through the off side for a single
quicker through the air, bowled flat outside off, nudged down towards short third
excellent shot, gave it some air on the off stump, he charged down the track and drove it uppishly inside -out between long-off and deep cover
poor bowling, long hop on middle, Gibbs has no trouble pulling it away wide of deep square leg for successive fours
pushed back past the bowler off the front foot for a single
struck powerfully but straight to the fielder in the direction of wide long-off
good length outside off and takes the inside edge as it spins into Kallis
struck away towards deep cover off the front foot
turned into the leg side, bowled a touch full on middle and leg
short outside off, Gibbs waited for it to spin into him and nudged it behind point for a single
short of a length on leg stump, rolled his wrists over it to play it down wide of fine leg
punched back to the bowler this time, bowled slightly short on the off stump
good length outside off and gets a hint of away movement to beat Gibbs as he tries to edge that wide of the keeper
full and wide, but not enough for the umpire to call it, Gibbs chases it fro the crease and misses, a harsh decision there
pushed to the covers off the front foot, a touch wide of the off stump
misfield and he concedes four! Laughlin's the culprit, short on the off and he swats it wide of deep square leg where Laughlin allows it to roll through his legs
short of a length, run down to third man for a single
on middle and off, turned away wide of square leg for a single
reaches forward and pushes it wide of cover
on the off stump, spinning in, paddled down to fine leg
quicker on middle and off, pushed off the back foot into the off side for a single
flighted outside off, looks to sweep that in front of square but fails to reach it, Haddin takes off the bails this time but Gibbs never left his crease
full on the off stump, driven firmly and all along the ground to long-off
good length on the off stump, comes forward and pushes that past point for a single
short of a length on the off, chopped down behind the stumps, Gibbs sends him back as he calls for a single
short again, dabbed behind point for a single
landed on a good length outside off, driven forcefully through to deep cover
back of a length on the off, punched to cover
short on the off stump, dropped short of point
tossed up on the off stump, turned wide of midwicket for a single
quicker one on the off,  comes down and dabs it to midwicket
full on the off, swept to deep midwicket
driven straight to the same fielder, on middle and off and he fails to bet the infield
does so well this time, driving through the line and playing it much straighter to long-on
tickled off the pads wide of square leg for a single
good length on the off stump, eased through the off side towards deep cover
back of a length on the off, dropped down short of Clarke at point, tries to catch Kallis off-guard at the non-striker's end with a shy at the stumps but he's well in
just a fraction short on the off stump, he charges forward and just pushes it firmly wide of mid-off, all timing there and it raced along the lush outfield

almost caught, a stunning effort from Laughlin at fine leg as Gibbs attempts a pull and it flies off the top edge, he catches it right at the edge and throws it back in just as he realises he is tripping backwards, saved five runs there, Gibbs though, survives
driven on the up to cover on the front foot
angling it into the right hander, pushed towards midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg, is down the track and turns it in front of square
flighted on the off, flicked wristily to square leg
dabbed behind point off the back foot for a single to bring up the 150
bowled much flatter, landed on a good length outside off and spun back in to strike Gibbs in line with middle and leg as he got down one one knee to sweep that powerfully in the square-leg region
shout for lbw, tossed up outside off, gets outside the line to drive it past midwicket, is hit on the pads but we know that can't be given
lands on the off and spins in, gets to the pitch and drives it down to long-on
good length outside off, gets forward and drives it on the up to deep cover
short of a length outside off, chopped down towards deep cover for a single
landed outside off, swung away a hint, left alone
fullish on the off, gets to the pitch and mistimes a drive to mid-off, gets a single though
short of a length, bends low and cuts it away to deep cover again, the new man is into the act already, getting singles easily and giving the strike to a well-settled Kallis

full and wide and he cashes in, leaning forward and square-driving it well wide of deep cover, moves to his 50 with that shot, an excellent innings that has kept South Africa well in the hunt after the loss of Smith
tossed up outside off, gets his front foot across and works it away to fine leg
quicker ball bowled full on the off, presents the full face to push it back to the bowler
held it back a touch, tried to push it past midwicket, was struck on the pads
finds the gap this time, driving it wide of midwicket for a single
tossed up outside off, paddled down fine
short of a length outside off and coming back in, dropped short of point for a single
driven off the front foot through the covers for a single
short of a length on the off, punched through to deep cover
four more, Kallis is moving along nicely here, short of a length, slashes it past the diving keeper, he intended it to go in that direction and placed it well to beat a diving Johnson at third man
length ball on the off, driven towards deep cover
good length outside of, wafts at it blindly, predictably misses
back of a length on the off, punched down to deep cover to keep the strike
full on the off, driven straight to cover
flighted on the off stump, bunts it down to deep cover off the front foot
bowled flat and short on middle, punched to the same fielder again
deep cover's been kept busy this time, gets forward and drives through the infield
driven down the ground to long-on
flat and quick outside off, slashed wide of deep point for a single
back of a length outside off, run down to third man
full and wide, slashes hard, flies off the outside edge to third man
slightly short on the off stump, makes room and square-drives it between deep cover and deep point for a handy couple
full on the off stump, driven firmly but straight to mid-off
short of a length outside off, swatted to short cover, mistimed it completely
looks to bunt it past cover, gets a thick inside edge on the leg side and they scamper a single as Bracken runs forward and tries to kick it onto the stumps
lands it short on the off, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
flat and full on the off, comes down the track and drives it down to long-on
short of a length, bringing it back into Kallis, blocked short of point for a single
driven firmly off the front foot to long-on
punched to deep cover off the back foot
pushed in short on middle and leg and spinning further down, de Villiers moves across to whip it past square leg, is rapped on the pads, but that came off the inside edge
came back in, drew Kallis forward with a good length ball on the off stump but he adjusted well to the movement to defend it back to the bowler
eased through the off side towards deep cover for a single
could this be the turning point? Bowled on a length outside off, sucking Kallis into the drive, angling away from him, gets a thick edge and Haddin stretches well to his right snap a sharp chance
full on the off stump, defended solidly back to the bowler
driven crisply off the front foot but straight to short cover
good length on the off stump, run down to third man for a single
full on middle, clips it off his pads uppishly wide of deep midwicket for a couple
back of a length on the off and moving away, tries to run it past the slip fielder towards third man, misses
short on the off, mistimes a pull in front of square towards mid-on
short on middle again, moves across to paddle it square but is hit on the thighs, signs of desperation here
falls into the trap, Johnson fires it in wide, it's a teasing driving length and Duminy is tempted, he goes at it hard leaning forward, gets a faint nick straight to Haddin
swinging in, length ball on the off stump, pushed to mid-off
good length on the off, shaping it away from the batsman, defended into the leg side
moved it back in, short of a length, not too much room, tries to chop it towards point, misses
bunts it towards Clarke at point and rushes for a single, would have been a close call had the attempted shy at the stumps at the non-striker's end been accurate
good length outside off and moving back in just a hint, but it was missing off as it struck him on the pads while playing forward
pushed off the front foot towards cover for a single
good length outside off, gets front and across and drives it wide of deep midwicket for a couple
short on middle, tries to whip it away fine, lobs up off the thighs into the leg side and they sneak  a quick single
back of a length, cut away hard into the ground and it bounces over Clarke for a single towards deep point
short of a length, slashes it wide of point and third man for a couple to bring up the 200

landing on the off stump and moving back in towards middle, punched off the back foot wide of midwicket, Ponting slides and throws it back to Johnson but Boucher has made it comfortably back for the second
lucky, and he'll take it, full and wide, reached forward for a drive, got an inside edge wide of the keeper to the fine-leg boundary
good length on the off stump, driven on the up towards mid-off and they grab a single
short of a length, kept a little low, chopped it down towards deep cover for a single
nippy, jagged back in after landing short of a good length outside off, tries to nudge it down to third man, misses
lands short on the off, dropped short of cover, decides against the single
full and wide, makes room, just about manages to reach it as it moves away a hint, gets the bottom of the bat to beat the keeper and third man to the boundary,streaky
the ball seemed to stop on him a little there, he was already into the shot, ended up just chipping it over the infield wide of mid-off
back of a length on the off, punched to mid-on who runs in to prevent the single

big wicket! Australia are in front now, short on the off stump, pulled away well but straight to Hauritz at deep midwicket positioned there exactly for that shot. The bowling change yields a wicket immediately, and it's up to AB and Albie now to pull things back for the hosts
back of a length on the off, defended off the back foot to the bowler
gets back and turns it in front of square
He's away, fraction short outside off, creams it to deep cover
slower ball bowled short outside off, dabbed to third man
short of a length, makes room and chops it wide of cover, mistimed but keeps the strike
slower ball, at 113.2 kmph, bowled full on the off, driven uppishly to long-off
back of a length on the off and moving away, punched to cover
cut away for his second boundary, that will relieve the pressure a little, banged in short outside off, cut away powerfully to beat deep cover and deep point
full on the off, drags it down to deep square leg for a single
short outside off, Albie leaps to swat that wide of short cover for a couple
full and wide, drives hard at it, fails to get his bat down in time, misses
short of a length on the off and spinning in, whipped away to deep square leg

Laughlin, you genius!! Tossed up outside off, and Albie goes for the slog-sweep, Laughlin's right at the edge of the ropes at deep midwicket and for a good while it appears the ball will clear him easily, but he waits, and times his jump to perfection to snap that over his head inches in front of the ropes, and celebrates kicking it Aussie-rules style back into the field. A decisive moment, that
flighted on middle and leg, driven down to deep midwicket for a single
short of a length on middle, reaches forward to block it into the leg side
short of a length outside off, cut away behind point for a couple, the task has gotten tougher now
Timber! Full and straight, de Villiers makes room to drive that through the covers, misses and the stumps are pegged back.
superb shot, full on middle and leg, the field is in and he just chips it wide of mid-on for a boundary off his first ball, well done
short of a length on the off, tries to force it through the off side, gets a thick edge wide of third man for a single, should have tried hard for the second there
full and wide, struck firmly but straight to the bowler, Laughlin doesn't field it cleanly and they scamper for a single
full outside off, dug out wide of point, fails to get the single
bouncer banged in short down the leg side, Morkel ducks and earns a wide
dragged it short on the off, mistimes a pull over mid-on but gets a couple for his efforts

What now, my friend? Short outside off, tried to upper-cut that over the third-man boundary, got it a lot squarer and certainly not the distance he desired, Bracken was waiting for it and took it gleefully at deep point, took some time to come down but he judged it well

Almost over now, pushes it into the off side and sets off for a single when there is none, gets no response from the non-striker, Steyn has run to the other end and is stranded, Hussey fields at short cover and throws it back to Haddin who completes the formalities
good length on the off and moving in, pushed into the leg side for a single
short and wide, goes for the cut, fails to make contact
comes back in to strike Morkel in the ribs as he tries to play it into the off side
yorker on middle, dug out wide of point for a single to keep the strike
full toss outside off, goes at it hard, edges it to Haddin who fails to take it on the bounce, allows it to go through his legs for a couple
straying on the pads, struck away to deep midwicket
bouncer banged in short on the off stump, Ntini ducks well
pushed wide of mid-off for a single to give the better batsman the strike
length ball on the off stump, picks it up well, striking it cleanly between deep midwicket and long-on
full toss on the off stump, smashed straight to cover who rockets a throw back in to prevent the single
bouncer banged in on middle, Ntini ducks and the crowd boos at the aggression shown by the Australian bowler
follows up with one that's bowled on a good length outside leg, raps him on the pads as he tries to play it on the leg side
superb stuff, what a reply after that bouncer, full and wide, just chipped it hard, timed it beautifully over the ropes wide of long-off, the crowd breaks out into a massive cheer
too wide, well outside off and Ntini wisely lets it go
cramps him on the crease with a good length ball on middle, plays it well, dropping it into the vacant leg-side field for a single
it's all over! Length ball on the off stump, tries to clear the long-on boundary but mistimes it completely, David Hussey runs back a few steps from mid-on to complete a simple catch
